\end{document}
```

**Explanation:**

1. The `\documentclass{article}` command specifies the document class, which determines the overall layout and formatting of the document.
2. The `\begin{document}` and `\end{document}` commands mark the beginning and end of the document content.
3. The `\tableofcontents` command generates the table of contents. This command should be placed before the first section or chapter in the document.
4. The `\section`, `\subsection`, etc. commands define the headings and sections of the document. Note that each section or subsection should have a unique label (e.g., `\label{sec:intro}`) to allow LaTeX to reference it in the TOC.
5. When you compile the document using LaTeX (e.g., `pdflatex mydoc.tex`), the TOC will be generated automatically and inserted at the location of the `\tableofcontents` command.

**Output:**

